<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1932-12-19T18:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1932-12-19T18:00:00-05:00" n="217" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d217">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">724.3415/2626a Supp.: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                        State</gloss> to the Ambassador in Brazil (<persName corresp="#p_MEV1" type="to">Morgan</persName>)</hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-12-19T18:00:00-05:00">December 19, 1932—6 p.m.</date>
                                </dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>97. Department’s circular December 15th. What action is Brazilian
                                Government taking? Brazilian and Honduran Governments are the only
                                ones which so far have not advised Neutral Commission of their
                                wholehearted support.</p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <persName corresp="#p_CWR1">
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Castle</hi>
                                    </persName>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>